{
  "stem": "2578.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In a sense, it was a fact that he did.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But at the same time, nowadays, I mean, now, in hindsight, you have a better way of reflecting on these days to realize and to understand his condition as opposed to the general opinion of the population of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was still a large controversy going on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it is very difficult to actually-- to understand and to realize whose fault it was, and who was right, and who was wrong under these circumstances.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In essence, he had no choice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His argument was-- his argument was, and it was a fact, that if the Jewish police, under his orders, came into the Jewish houses and took out the Jews, he took them out.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, the police took them out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If the German SS came in to took-- to take out the Jews from the houses, they were tortured.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They would kill them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If somebody was hiding, they would be shot on the spot.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So the reasoning and the argument of the leader, Rumkowski, of the ghetto, was that if I am doing it, which I am forced to do it, I am doing something that it will be done anyway with less casualties.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My personal opinion, it is difficult to say.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Judging from-- I mean, today, by reading and by listening to people who lived through these-- these times in different areas, I would say that Rumkowski is supposed to take the example of, let's say, the same leader of the Warsaw ghetto and from other ghettos.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That they committed suicide in order not to have on-- on their conscience that they sent Jews to death camps.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- we thought, and we were sure at that time, that he knew exactly where the Jews are being sent.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
